  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/sensitivity/hemolysis-sa",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis — hemolysis model parameters",
    "description": "Sobol' indices were computed for five input parameters (hematocrit, fluid dynamic viscosity, inlet pressure, rotational speed, and power-law exponent α) over the declared operating envelope using 4096 quasi-random samples. Rotational speed and power-law exponent α together account for 74% of total hemolysis index variance (first-order Sobol' indices 0.48 and 0.26 respectively), confirming that model form uncertainty in the hemolysis constitutive law is the dominant epistemic contributor; this finding directly informed the elevated requiredLevel for Model form and drove additional validation at high-shear operating points."
  },
